<title>INDIA: India Infoys up seven pct on fund buying.</title>
<headline>India Infoys up seven pct on fund buying.</headline>
<text>
<p>BOMBAY, June 10 (Reuter) Shares of Indian software firm, Infosys Technologies rose 119.50 rupees, or about seven percent, to 1,760 on Tuesday on buying by foreign funds, traders said.</p>
<p>The company's board of directors last week approved an increase in the foreign institutional investor holding limit in the firm to 30 percent from 24 percent.</p>
